\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 What This Means\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The philosophy stated earlier \'97 
\f2\i things are not worth less in the future because of interest; they are worth different amounts in the future because of uncertainty about when the future arrives
\f0\i0  \'97 is now a theorem, not a belief.\
It is captured precisely by the identity:\
$$\\underbrace\{e^\{-r(T-t)\}\}
\f2\i \{\\text\{conventional: time costs money\}\} = \\underbrace\{\\int_t^T e^\{-\\int_t^s \\kappa , du\} \\cdot \\kappa , ds\}
\f0\i0 \{\\text\{Islamic: uncertainty resolves over time\}\}$$\
Both sides integrate to the same number when r = \uc0\u954  and T \u8594  \u8734 . They are numerically equivalent but philosophically opposite. One treats time as a commodity that earns rent. The other treats time as an information process that resolves uncertainty.\
The Baraka protocol is not a DeFi application built on someone else's mathematics. It is the first implementation layer of a complete and self-consistent alternative to interest-based value theory \'97 one that was waiting inside the Ackerer paper to be found.\
